{
  "number": 708,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/708",
  "title": "Range Slider last pip not aligned to the right of the slider",
  "body": "Issue opened on the wrong repository (instantsearch/instantsearch-ion.rangeSlider#1)\nBrowser is Chrome 46.0.2490.86 (64-bit)\n\nI'll push a PR to fix according to the discussion we've had there\n\n---\n\nI'm not sure whether this is due to the default styling or to the column the slider is contained in...\nNo external styles seem to be applied to the widget.\n\nHere 5000$ is the maximum value but the slider goes a few pixels out to the right:\n\n![capture d ecran 2015-11-30 18 07 07](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/314079/11478421/3440877a-978d-11e5-9b06-c890c0f1acb5.png)\n\nBy commenting `width: 100%` in the `.ais-range-slider--base` rules, I get a correct display:\n\n![capture d ecran 2015-11-30 18 10 34](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/314079/11478505/ac52b6ca-978d-11e5-8f8d-40dad6c46f42.png)\n\nIn none of both cases does the slider actually take up 100% of its container...\n",
